OL,3,CSchool worker who says she was sacked
OL,4,Cfor being Christian wins right to
OL,5,Cappeal
OL,7,FMrs Higgs, supported by the Christian
OL,8,FLegal Centre, took the school to an
OL,9,Femployment tribunal, arguing she had
OL,10,Fbeen unlawfully discriminated against
OL,11,Fbecause of her Christian beliefs.
OL,13,FThe school had denied dismissing the
OL,14,Fmother of two because of her religious
OL,15,Fbeliefs and said she was sacked
OL,16,Fbecause of the language used in the
OL,17,Fposts.
